FBIS4-61673 "drsov089_n_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-089 Daily Report 6 May 1994 Turkmenistan Russian Border Issues Discussed in Ashgabat Russian Border Issues Discussed in Ashgabat LD0605214994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1230 GMT 6 May 94 LD0605214994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Kurbanova] [Text] Ashgabat, 6 May -- The joint protection of Turkmenistan's state border was discussed today during a meeting between Turkmenistan President Saparmurad Niyazov and Lieutenant General Aleksandr Bespalov, deputy commander of the Russian Federation border troops. Methods were defined for the implementation of the intergovernment treaty between Turkmenistan and Russia, signed at the end of 1993, on the joint protection of Turkmenistan's borders, and on the status of Russian Federation servicemen in the Republic. Aleksandr Bespalov said "the formation of an operational group of Russian border troops which is being set up in accordance with the intergovernment treaty, has been completed." Issues related to insuring the functioning of the operational group in close cooperation with the Turkmenistan border troops were also examined at the meeting. This kind of cooperation meets the mutual interests of the two countries and insures their security at Turkmenistan's state border.
